info.title: ca.boundaries.io
info.description: CA Postal Code(ex. T6H, or A0A0A1 ), FSA and LDU, Boundaries API: A simple & very fast API that will allow you to integrate multiple GeoJson CA FSA and LDU level boundaries result into your apps and systems. This API is designed to be used programatically for optimal performance. When using the MashApe UI for queries expect significant latency issues on large result sets!

tags.name: Query by LDU Code
tags.description:
We return Hexagons based on the H3 Hexagon grid for geo spatial:
You can use the h3-index for fine grained Geo Spatial analysis. 

More information seen the below links:
https://eng.uber.com/h3

https://www.safe.com/webinars/hexagonify-the-world-the-theory-and-applications-of-uber-h3/

parameters.name: resolution
parameters.description:
What is H3 resolution?
10 is the H3 resolution, between 0 (coarsest) and 15 (finest). The coordinates entered are the latitude and longitude, in degrees, you want the index for (these coordinates are the Statue of Liberty). You should get an H3 index as output, like 8a2a1072b59ffff

get.description:
Query for Boundary by H3Index.
Query for a LDU boundary by H3 Index, if a LDU Postal Code does not exist within the H3 Index Hexagon, an empty FeatureCollection is returned.

**H3Index resolution must be greater than 8.**
